                <head>The Warmest Day.</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>"Old Sol is laying it on to us poor critters."</excerpt>
                <transcript>
                    <p>--Saturday last was the warmest day this summer; the Thermometer at Mr.
                        Heyser's Drug Store stood at 92 degrees in the shade! On the 10th day of
                        July it had reached 90 degrees. Old Sol is laying it on to us poor
                    critters.</p>
